# HVF Nexus On-Site Activation Protocol

## 1. Hardware Initialization
- Deploy Industrial IoT Gateways at Sector 1 (HelioGrid Hub).
- Establish Secure Local Area Network (SLAN) with WPA3 Enterprise encryption.
- Connect Physical Sensors (Voltage, Amperage, GPS) to Gateway via Modbus.

## 2. Nexus Handshake
- Authenticate Gateway using CEO-issued Unique Device ID (UDI).
- Execute 'Nexus-Connect' script to sync local data with Cloud Master.
- Verify real-time telemetry appears on the Tactical Site Map (TSM).

## 3. Personnel Integration
- Provision Tier 1 & Tier 2 credentials via the Nexus Admin Portal.
- Conduct local stress test: Toggle a non-critical load (e.g., perimeter lighting) 
  via the Nexus interface.

## 4. Sovereignty Check
- Test the 'Omega' bypass. Ensure the CEO UUID can lock/unlock the sector 
  independently of local Superintendent access.
